In a #medium pot{}, bring 5 cups water (8 cups for 4 servings) to a boil, then
reduce to a low simmer.

Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and dice @yellow onion{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add
onion; cook until slightly softened and lightly browned, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add
@Italian chicken sausage mix{9%oz} and cook, breaking up meat into pieces,
until browned, ~{3-4%minutes} more.

Add @Arborio rice{3/4%cup}, @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings), and a big
pinch of @salt{1/2%tsp} (1 tsp for 4). Cook, stirring frequently, until rice is
translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add 1 cup simmering water and @chicken stock concentrate{2} to pan with rice
mixture; stir until liquid has mostly absorbed. Repeat with remaining simmering
water—adding ½ cup at a time and stirring until liquid has mostly absorbed—until
rice is al dente, sausage is cooked through, and risotto is creamy,
~{25-30%minutes}.

> Depending on the size of your pan, you may need a little more or a little
> less liquid for the risotto. If you prefer your risotto a little more al
> dente, cook for less time.

== Whipped Ricotta & Toppings ==

Dice @tomato{1}.

Roughly chop @parsley{1/4%oz}.

Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

In a #medium bowl{}, whisk @ricotta cheese{4%oz} with a squeeze of lemon juice
(big squeeze for 4 servings), @olive oil{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4), and a pinch of
@salt{} and @pepper{} until light and fluffy. Taste and add more lemon juice,
salt, and pepper if desired.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #medium pan{} over high heat. Add
tomato and cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly charred,
~{1-2%minutes}. Transfer to a #plate{} and season with salt and pepper.

Once risotto is done, remove from heat and stir in @cream cheese{4%tbsp}, half
the parsley, @butter{2%tbsp} (4 TBSP for 4 servings), and lemon zest to taste.

> If risotto is too thick, stir in another splash of water.

Taste and season generously with salt and pepper.

Divide risotto between plates. Top with whipped ricotta, blistered tomato, and
remaining parsley. Season with pepper. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on
the side.

> Chicken Sausage is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.